reviews.review: The Rise of Skywalker was the most disappointing movie of the year. There was way too much going on and it felt as if it wanted to please everyone. What we got in the end was an over crowded end to the Skywalker saga.

This movie failed to right the wrongs of Last Jedi. It is obvious that they rushed it. There should have been more back story for at least 3 characters. Instead you got almost none on 2 of them and absolutely none on the 3rd. They could have spent 15 minutes on a little more detail and the movie would have been substantially better. It's like Disney just wanted to get this one over with after the horrifically bad reviews of Last Jedi.
42 years after seeing the first movie Episode 4.  I finally watched the conclusion.  It was a good series, but it lasted a really long time.
Don't listen to the critics. It was the perfect ending. Lando's cameo was a bit gratuitous, but otherwise it was just the right balance between old and new. Awesome movie.

There's a lot going on and its incohesive at times, but this movie is great. The acting from our main characters is some of the best we've seen in any SW film, the story is true to SW form, and the action is intense.

Had flaws, but made up for them by ret-conning some of the awful choices made in the last movie.

This movie was made up of a series of vignettes that were loosely tied together with minimal effort put towards dialogue and character development. 

It doesn't feel like a sequel to either The Force Awakens or The Last Jedi, which is the weirdest part because helped write and directed the Force Awakens. Most of the movie was throwing out things set up in both movies with quick, careless decisions.

I honestly think that JJ Abrams just superficially apes movies and television scenes that he has seen before without bothering to put them into a proper context of a larger narrative. You could rearrange most of this movie and lose none of the narrative, mostly because it's a very weak narrative.
